title: avoid class minification and obfuscation and  Gson().fromJson null value in release mode
message:
avoid class minification and obfuscation and  Gson().fromJson null value in release mode

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/30001674/gson-deserialize-null-pointer-in-released-apk
in release mode proguard change props names and then _ final Results results = new Gson().fromJson(result, Results.class);_ returns null value.
Solved problem for release mode scan -- issue was due gson.fromJson with minified/obfuscated class model

title: Merge pull request #7 from ZKjellberg/tweaks
message:
Merge pull request #7 from ZKjellberg/tweaks

Long list of improvements

title: Added null value check for destination to save resource calls to Picasso.…
message: Added null value check for destination to save resource calls to Picasso. Picasso doesn't complain about null requests interestingly.

title: Retaining a static reference to the last destination used. This allows state to…
message: Retaining a static reference to the last destination used. This allows state to be saved for rotation.

title: Fixed issue with Picasso refreshing images. The image variable's path was never…
message:
Fixed issue with Picasso refreshing images. The image variable's path was never updated. It will now generate a new path for each image, allowing a refresh.
Centered TextView contents.

title: Better screenshot.
message:
Better screenshot.
Increased font size for result.

title: Large list of changes.
message:
Large list of changes.
1. New permission implementation. App now checks whenever user makes a request. Upon confirming permission, app initiates processing request
2. Updated the TextView output with better formatting
.4 New App Icon using Android Studio Image Generator Tool
5. New Screenshot for README, with Nexus 6P frame using Android Studio Screenshot Tool
6. Added freezesText to TextView XML which stores state for rotation
7. onActivityResult did not require FileReader, which also means the try/catch was unnecessary
8. Replaced hard link path to internal data with the proper method call to discover
9. Removed WRITE_INTERNAL_STORAGE as this permission does not exist
10. Updated TextView text on failure
